16 requester'
17 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
18 number to read consecutively.
19 SUMMARY
2200 This amendment provides that a body, agency or official may file an action in the
2211 Superior Court for an order of protection from a request or series of requests for inspection
2222 or copying that is unduly burdensome or oppressive within 60 days of the date on which
2233 the body, agency or official notifies the requester that a series of public records requests is
2244 unduly burdensome or oppressive.
